I need to identify the line item that represents an increase in taxes accrued but not yet paid.

Looking at the cash flow statement, I can see there's a line item called "Increase (Decrease) in Tax Payable" with an amount of 287762.05. 

Tax payable represents taxes that have been accrued but not yet paid. Since this value is positive, it indicates an increase in tax payable, which means there's an increase in the amount of taxes accrued but not yet paid.

Therefore, the value of the increase in tax accrued but not yet paid is 287762.05.

{"solution": {'value': '287762.05'} }
